---
description: Database schema and migration conventions
globs: src/db/**/*.ts, drizzle/**
---

- Schema lives in src/db/schema.ts (split by domain if it exceeds ~300 lines).
- Naming: snake_case columns, plural table names. Every table has id (uuid,
  default random), created_at, updated_at.
- Tenant-owned tables include org_id (FK → organizations.id, indexed, not null).
- Add an index for every foreign key and every common query path. Justify each.
- Soft delete (deleted_at) only where the spec requires recovery; otherwise
  hard delete.
- Migration workflow: edit schema → `pnpm db:generate` → REVIEW the generated
  SQL → commit schema + migration together. Never edit applied migrations;
  never push schema changes without a migration file.
- Queries live in src/db/queries/ (shared) or a module's queries.ts/service.ts — never inline SQL in components
  or actions.
